Scientific-Atlanta Inc. said it has been awarded contracts valued at $36 million to install satellite network programs abroad. 

The telecommunications company also said it is expanding its digital international satellite communications product line. 

Scientific-Atlanta said it was awarded a $29 million contract to install a large digital satellite telephone network and a 100-site interactive data network in Chile.
The company said it also received a $7 million contract to provide a major international gateway network in Gabon. 

In its expanded product line, the company said it is producing turnkey digital earth station systems that support applications for voice, video, and data transmission. 

